#67 [steel-hammer-minio 16/16] RUN mc --help
#67 0.686 NAME:
#67 0.686   mc - MinIO Client for object storage and filesystems.
#67 0.686 
#67 0.687 USAGE:
#67 0.688   mc [FLAGS] COMMAND [COMMAND FLAGS | -h] [ARGUMENTS...]
#67 0.688 
#67 0.688 COMMANDS:
#67 0.688   alias      manage server credentials in configuration file
#67 0.688   admin      manage MinIO servers
#67 0.688   anonymous  manage anonymous access to buckets and objects
#67 0.688   batch      manage batch jobs
#67 0.688   cp         copy objects
#67 0.688   cat        display object contents
#67 0.688   cors       manage bucket CORS configuration
#67 0.688   diff       list differences in object name, size, and date between two buckets
#67 0.688   du         summarize disk usage recursively
#67 0.688   encrypt    manage bucket encryption config
#67 0.688   event      manage object notifications
#67 0.688   find       search for objects
#67 0.688   get        get s3 object to local
#67 0.688   head       display first 'n' lines of an object
#67 0.688   ilm        manage bucket lifecycle
#67 0.688   idp        manage MinIO IDentity Provider server configuration
#67 0.688   license    license related commands
#67 0.688   legalhold  manage legal hold for object(s)
#67 0.688   ls         list buckets and objects
#67 0.688   mb         make a bucket
#67 0.688   mv         move objects
#67 0.688   mirror     synchronize object(s) to a remote site
#67 0.688   od         measure single stream upload and download
#67 0.688   ping       perform liveness check
#67 0.688   pipe       stream STDIN to an object
#67 0.688   put        upload an object to a bucket
#67 0.688   quota      manage bucket quota
#67 0.688   rm         remove object(s)
#67 0.688   retention  set retention for object(s)
#67 0.688   rb         remove a bucket
#67 0.688   replicate  configure server side bucket replication
#67 0.688   ready      checks if the cluster is ready or not
#67 0.688   sql        run sql queries on objects
#67 0.688   stat       show object metadata
#67 0.688   support    support related commands
#67 0.688   share      generate URL for temporary access to an object
#67 0.688   tree       list buckets and objects in a tree format
#67 0.688   tag        manage tags for bucket and object(s)
#67 0.688   undo       undo PUT/DELETE operations
#67 0.688   update     update mc to latest release
#67 0.688   version    manage bucket versioning
#67 0.688   watch      listen for object notification events
#67 0.688   
#67 0.688 GLOBAL FLAGS:
#67 0.688   --autocompletion                 install auto-completion for your shell
#67 0.688   --config-dir value, -C value     path to configuration folder (default: "/opt/minio/.mc") [$MC_CONFIG_DIR]
#67 0.688   --quiet, -q                      disable progress bar display [$MC_QUIET]
#67 0.688   --disable-pager, --dp            disable mc internal pager and print to raw stdout [$MC_DISABLE_PAGER]
#67 0.688   --no-color                       disable color theme [$MC_NO_COLOR]
#67 0.688   --json                           enable JSON lines formatted output [$MC_JSON]
#67 0.688   --debug                          enable debug output [$MC_DEBUG]
#67 0.688   --resolve value                  resolves HOST[:PORT] to an IP address. Example: minio.local:9000=10.10.75.1 [$MC_RESOLVE]
#67 0.688   --insecure                       disable SSL certificate verification [$MC_INSECURE]
#67 0.688   --limit-upload value             limits uploads to a maximum rate in KiB/s, MiB/s, GiB/s. (default: unlimited) [$MC_LIMIT_UPLOAD]
#67 0.688   --limit-download value           limits downloads to a maximum rate in KiB/s, MiB/s, GiB/s. (default: unlimited) [$MC_LIMIT_DOWNLOAD]
#67 0.688   --custom-header value, -H value  add custom HTTP header to the request. 'key:value' format.
#67 0.688   --help, -h                       show help
#67 0.688   --version, -v                    print the version
#67 0.688   
#67 0.688 TIP:
#67 0.688   Use 'mc --autocompletion' to enable shell autocompletion
#67 0.688 
#67 0.688 COPYRIGHT:
#67 0.688   Copyright (c) 2015-2025 MinIO, Inc.
#67 0.688 
#67 0.688 LICENSE:
#67 0.688   GNU AGPLv3 <https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html>
